{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother pointed to the books, took out the book, and she said to me, 'Itkele, when you're going to learn how to read, you're going to find a treasure here.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You can sit right here in Ciechonw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You will travel through the world, through the ages, with the greatest mind, everything.' She made it so amazing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the reason why she had it locked when we were very little is because I was the oldest of three children, and I was still a little girl.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she was afraid that the little children might damage the book.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Later on, when we became older, it was open.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when I learned to-- eagerly to read Yiddish, I was devouring the Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she read me all kinds of stories.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But one story that really became, later, relevant to my life was the story called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She read it in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's called It was written by a Yiddish, Leib Peretz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And briefly, I'd like to share that story, because it was very relevant later to my life.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was thinking about it a lot during the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was about a boy, whose name was Bontsha, but, unfortunately, lost his mother when he was a little child.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "His father took another wife when he was 13 years old, which was a very cruel woman and constantly abused Bontsha.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She would begrudge him the food while she ate very well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She would not give him clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He never had a friend.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He was lonely.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the coldest winter time, she would chase him out barefoot to chop wood, and all those things.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she-- and Bontsha was suffering.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But he never complained.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He was always silent.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And that's why the [INAUDIBLE] called him Bontsha the silent.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
